<h2>Learn</h2>

<ul>
<li><a href="/forums/showthread.php?t=84210"><strong>The Forum's Rules</strong></a> - must read!</li>

<li><a href="/forums/showthread.php?t=3450215"><strong>Ask an Uber Question, Get an Uber Answer</strong></a> is your go-to place if you have any questions about the tier.</li>

<li><a href="/forums/forumdisplay.php?f=149"><strong>The Ubers Analyses Forum</strong></a> is the place to go for writing analyses. You may reserve an analysis in the <a href="/forums/showthread.php?t=3468516">Index Thread</a> or comment on analyses that are a WIP.</li>

<li>Arceus has many formes&mdash;17 to be exact&mdash;but not all are given enough credit. <strong><a href="/forums/showthread.php?t=3481350">Arceus: Deity Of Underrated Sets</a></strong> project brings up Arceus's most obscure sets and forms to public recognition and explains how to use them, in order to give Arceus its much deserved credit.</li>

<li>In <strong><a href="/forums/showthread.php?t=3473048">the Ubers Replay Thread</a></strong> you can share and watch amazing battles related to Ubers.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Participate</h2>

<ul>
<li><strong><a href="http://mibbit.com/#ubers@irc.synirc.net">#ubers on synIRC</a></strong> is Smogon's splinter channel for the best metagame! Join this channel to discuss with a few of the best contributors of the Ubers community&mdash;don't hesitate bringing up a topic too, we don't bite! Click on the link to join the channel via Mibbit or go <a href="/irc/tutorials/mirc">here</a> for a mIRC guide.</li>

<li><strong><a href="/forums/showthread.php?t=3466707">Project Ubers 2.0</a></strong> was brought up by Theorymon back in DPP, and was created to increase creativity in our static tier. This did not change when the fifth generation was released; Ubers is still a static tier, and Project Ubers gives creativity a shot. The sets in the project's database have been tested and are viable in the tier.</li>

<div style="float: right; margin-left: 10px;"><img src="/media/upload/tiers/ubers/quazabyyilx.png" title="by Yilx" alt="" /></div>

<li>In the <strong><a href="/forums/showthread.php?t=3449887">Ubers Combination Thread</a></strong>, much like Ubers Teambuilding, we showcase and collect the tier's greatest combinations of Pokemon. If you want to build a new team and are looking for inspiration, this is the thread to go to!</li>

<li>The <strong><a href="/forums/showthread.php?t=3471695">Ubers Teambuilding</a></strong> thread assembles many of the tier's top-notch Pokemon and organizes them according to their roles so you can simply search the thread for a Pokemon that fits in your team!</li>

<li>Much like the Ubers Teambuilding thread and the Ubers CCAT, <strong><a href="/forums/showthread.php?t=3483063">Team Study</a></strong> showcases Ubers' best teams provided by Ubers' most skilled battlers, in order to bring up discussion and improve the teambuilding skills of the Ubers battlers.</li>

<li><strong><a href="/forums/showthread.php?t=3473976">The Ubers Viability Ranking Thread</a></strong> asks to rank Ubers' common Pokemon, be it from Kyogre up in S-Rank to Shedinja in E-Rank, every Pokemon that you find viable in Ubers should be listed. If the Pokemon in your mind is not listed&mdash;feel free to bring it up to discussion!</li>

<li><strong><a href="/forums/threads/the-ubers-role-comparison-project.3484561/">The Ubers Role Comparison Project</a></strong> compares and contrasts duos or trios of viable Pokemon in the metagame that have similar roles. If you are trying to decide which sweeper should you use&mdash;like Rayquaza or Arceus, or which wall should you use, this thread is just for you!</li>
</ul>

